ed)\n\nThere's no catalyst mentioned in this reaction.\n\nLet me format this as a condition_role_mapping:\n\n{\n  \"ClCCl\": \"solvent\",\n  \"O=C(OO)c1cccc(Cl)c1\": \"reagent\",\n  \"O=C1CCC2=C(N1)c1ccccc1CC2\": \"substrate\"\n}\n\nWait, the question asks for reagents, solvent, and catalyst. The substrate is the main reactant. Let me reconsider - in the context of condition role identification, typically we categorize:\n- Substrate: the main compound being transformed\n- Reagent: the compound that facilitates the transformation but is consumed\n- Solvent: the medium\n- Catalyst: speeds up reaction but is not consumed\n\nSo:\n- ClCCl (dichloromethane): solvent\n- O=C(OO)c1cccc(Cl)c1 (mCPBA): reagent\n- O=C1CCC2=C(N1)c1ccccc1CC2: substrate\n\nNo catalyst is present in this reaction."
